post_text: East Minico 6th graders...are you ready?
shared_text:
East Minico Middle School
August 16 at 6:20 PM ·

We are excited to welcome our 6th grade students on Tuesday, August 18 for orientation, which will take place from 8:05-1:00! We would ask that parents drop students off on the north side of the building, and refrain from entering the building if at all possible. Please call if you have specific questions or concerns, or set up an appointment to visit in person. We really appreciate your help in keeping the drop-off line moving as efficiently as possible, and for helping us keep visitors to the school as minimal as we can. Thanks for your support in this regard.

Access to student schedules will be available through PowerSchool on August 17. We will also be handing out schedules as students arrive on Tuesday morning. Students will need their backpack, a pencil, a water bottle, and a notebook. More specifics regarding supplies will be shared by classroom teachers. Devices will be handed out on August 20. Students will meet their teachers, take a tour of the school, meet with school administration, and eat lunch. We can’t wait! Let us know if you have any questions. Go Pirates!!

post_text:
On Site Registration
Tuesday at WEst Minico for students attending West Minico, Paul Elementary, and Heyburn Elementary.
We will be following CDC guidelines. We ask that those entering the building wear a mask, and to limit the number of people coming in. We will enforcing physical distancing, so lines may be longer.

FAQ:
1) How can I avoid long lines? Complete registration online!
2) Do I need to attend if I completed registration online? No- you do not need to come in person if registration is completed online.
3) I don't have a snapcode? Call in to your school secretary and they can get that for you. You can also get the snapcode on site and register at home if you would like.
4)Will schedules be finished? No - not all schedules are completed at this time. West Minico will not be handing out schedules.

July 28 at 3:02 PM ·

Interested in attending CSI in the fall? Our campus is open and we are ready to help you meet your goals! Join us for an Instant Enrollment Day on July 30th at our Twin Falls and Mini-Cassia locations. Get admitted, get advised, get registered for fall classes, and make a plan to pay for college all in one stop! Leave the event with your fall semester schedule and your CSI ID card. post_text: This is a great opportunity for our students coming into kindergarten this year.
shared_text:
Idaho State Department of Education
June 22 at 9:42 PM ·

Superintendent Sherri Ybarra invites parents to join the virtual event, Idaho Ready to Learn: Countdown to Kindergarten, happening June 23 and 24 via Facebook live! Idaho Ready to Learn is an exciting new program that supports parents of incoming kindergarten students. This program will kick off with a live, 2-day statewide event via the Idaho PTV Families Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/events/592325604822085/. During this event, professionals around the state (including Supt. Ybarra and the director of our Special Education department, Charlie Silva) will share important information, tips, tricks, and activities to help parents get their children excited for kindergarten. Topics will include academic, social, and motor skills, how to access public libraries, and more. The event will begin streaming at 10:30 each day.

Find more information about Idaho Ready to Learn and a weekly schedule of fun, educational activities for incoming kindergartners at www.idahoptv.org/ReadyToLearn.

post_text:
Meet Teresa Vargas
-She has been a teacher in the Minidoka County School district for 34 years!
-She has taught at Heyburn elementary for all 34 years!
-She has taught 1st grade for 25 years and 3rd grade for 9 years.
-Favorite memory: She vividly remembers a cute little first grade boy who was really struggling to learn to read, and just couldn't read more than a few sight words. She worked really hard with him, and one day he looked at her with a surprised look, said "Oh! Is that all I have to do?" and read. Within a few weeks he was reading far above grade level. It was literally like a light bulb turned on and he was a fluent reader.
Plans after retirement: She wants to travel a bit, do some volunteer work, help care for her mother, and enjoy whatever else she chooses to do!
Congratulations on your retirement from Minidoka County School District. We appreciate the many years of service you have provided in our district.

post_text:
La semana del 18 al 22 de mayo, realizaremos tareas de fin de año. Hemos programado horarios para que se recojan artículos personales, así como boletas de calificaciones, fotos, etc. En este momento, también necesitamos que se devuelvan todos los dispositivos, así como libros de texto, libros de la biblioteca y cualquier otro elemento que pertenezca a la escuela.
Se ha creado un horario para limitar el número de personas que ingresan al edificio a la vez. Consulte la imagen de abajo y vaya a la escuela de su hijo a la hora designada, alfabéticamente por apellido.
Reconocemos que algunos no podrán ir a la hora seleccionada, por lo que habrá dos opciones nocturnas. Seguiremos las pautas de distanciamiento social, así que tenga paciencia con nosotros. Lo alentamos a usar máscaras para su protección.
Las escuelas proporcionarán procedimientos y procesos específicos para cada una.

shared_text:
Idaho National Guard
May 12 at 2:45 PM ·

THANK YOU: On Friday we are teaming up with the Mountain Home Air Force Base Gunfighters to perform a flyover over 11 Idaho cities with two 124th Fighter Wing A-10 Thunderbolt IIs and two F-15Es in honor of Idaho's medical workers, first responders and all essential workers.

The flight path was selected to say thank you to a large number of the essential workers that have kept Idaho running during the COVID-19 pandemic. The mission provides the chance for active duty and National Guard pilots to fly together, demonstrating the close total force relationships the Idaho military community shares.

Residents should observe the flyover from the safety of their homes or worksite and should refrain from travelling to see the flyover. Social distancing should be practiced at all times.

post_text: South Central Public Health District would like families in our district to know that beginning this week, immunization appointments can be made for all ages. No walk-ins at this time, however. Buzz when arriving at the appointment and they will let you in. They will allow 30 minutes between appointments to make sure there is time to sanitize. Bring as few extra family members to the appointment as possible. To save time at the appointment, go to phd5.idaho.gov to fill out forms ahead of time. We hope this information helps your families to stay healthy. Remember that kindergartners, 7th graders, and now 12th graders all need certain immunizations before beginning next school year.

post_text: 💛❤️ #Classof2020
shared_text:
Kimberley Kidd is at Minico High School.
April 11 at 3:27 AM · Rupert, ID ·

Social Distancing and our Spartan family-
#BeTheLightID-what a wonderful hashtag during such a trying time. Tonight at 8:20 we turned on all the stadium lights- football, baseball and softball fields. They were on for 20 minutes as the students, parents, community and athletes were able to drive through our parking lots. They honked, they waved, they cheered and they smiled. I cried!! What a wonderful set of emotions to feel as we honored our students, athletes and Class of 2020. Thank you for coming..... I really needed to see you all. As hard as this is.... we are resilient, we will battle and we will get through this!!! I love my job, I love all of you and I love our Spartan family. We are in this together. We are #SpartanStrong! ♥️💛
Special thanks to Coach Trenkle,Ms. Smith, Mrs. Hobbs and our StuCo Senior Class Officers for all of their help putting this together. ♥️

post_text: Looking for a fun science activity? try this at home today.
shared_text:
Idaho STEM Action Center
March 25 at 3:30 PM ·

STEM@Home

Have your kids ever wondered where clouds come from? Try this experiment to show them how clouds are formed.

How to make a cloud in a jar using hairspray!

You will need the following materials:

A jar with lid
About 1/3 cup hot water
Ice
Hairspray

https://www.giftofcuriosity.com/weather-science-how-to-make-a-cloud-in-a-jar/

We can't wait to see how this experiment goes for your kiddos. Share pictures or comments to our FB page. We would love to hear from you!

For more STEM@Home learning resources go to our resource portal at: https://resources.stem.idaho.gov/

And Adult Supervision is advised for all experiments!

Check out Nate Larsen from KBOI demonstrating how to do this activity on the FB page at:
https://www.facebook.com/CBS2Boise

#STEMatHOME #CBS2

post_text:
Dear Parents/Patrons,
I wanted to let you know of some of the additional steps we are taking in response to concerns over the spread of the coronavirus that has been in the news recently.
Every bus was completely sanitized Monday before they went out that afternoon. We are also providing extra classroom supplies for cleaning and disinfecting desks, counter tops, doorknobs, keyboards and other hands-on items.
We ask for your support in making sure that your children are careful to follow proper hand hygiene, cough etiquette and staying home when sick. Please feel free to contact us if you have any further questions or concerns.
Dr. Kenneth Cox

There is a social media rumor going around that threats have been made at Mt.Harrison High School. When this was reported to school officials last week the school resource officer was brought in and an investigation conducted. It was determined that there were no threats made.

In an effort to ensure students feel safe, I have asked that a police officer be at Mt. Harrison tomorrow morning. If anyone has information that the District needs to be aware of please contact either Mr. Fairchild (jfairchild@minidokaschools.org) or myself (kcox@minidokaschools.org).
